       being between the Earth and Sun.

       location will remain there unless disturbed, whereupon it will move 
       away.  In practice, there will always be some disturbance. Further, 
       since the Sun is a radio source, communications with spacecraft at 
       L1 are difficult to pick out against the background noise. Thus, 
       spacecraft such as Genesis, WIND, SOHO, and ACE are placed in "halo" 
       orbits around the L1 point. SMART-1 flew through L1 prior to lunar
